Mahogany Run Delivery, Inc. Is a San Diego based furniture delivery company which caters to furniture stores and interior designers.  We provide pick up and drop off transportation services in Southern California. At our 10,000 Square foot warehouse we provide receiving, inspection, and storage services. In addition we offer custom coordinated moving and packing referral services catered to your needs specializing in art, collectibles, & placement engineering challenges.Our slogan "A Higher Level of Care" describes our service that has established a reputation for dependability as well as quality client care since 1999. Since then the company growth has been consistent & stable. We focus on customer service. Another value we charish is that a company is only as good as it's employees, we offer good pay, profit sharing & medical benefits, along with a positive and pleasant work environment, all very important. My job at MRD consists of business management, outside sales, special placement engineering, accounting & on-site coordination.

Wayne Back is one the best people I have met in my life. He is a respected business owner, philanthropist, and a man with immeasurable kindness.  I met him through my former client and employer, Stepping Stone of San Diego, Inc., a non profit organization Wayne has been lending his leadership to for about two decades. At the time we collaborated on fundraising and development projects for the agency, Wayne was serving his 4th consecutive team on the Board of Directors. He has also made significant donations to this and other San Diego charities. Check out the current edition of Modern Luxury’s Charity Date Book. It features a profile of Wayne Back and his company, a white glove furniture and art moving/storing company based in San Diego. I utilized his business, Mahogany Run Delivery, for a large moving project that had to be completed within one day. What can I say? The crew did not only get the job done, but everything was put in the right place at the new location - without a scratch and perfectly organized.Several times a year, Wayne donates high-end furniture and designer accessories from his warehouse inventory to hold estate sales that benefit charities. He has involved me in the capacity of marketing/promotions for several of them.In sum, anyone doing business with Wayne will be impressed by his style and commitment to professionalism. On a personal level, his generosity and dedication to his community will rub off on you.

summary: Growing up on a 7000 acre ranch in Northern California , I feel I'm in the perfect field! I love the transportation industry & running heavy equipment, yet at my job I don't have to get as dirty as working on the farm when I was younger. I learned a lot from my Dad working with him about business management & equipment preventative maintenance. I have many hands on mechanical abilities, with a can do attitude and a touch of MacGyver! I cultivate a positive productive and energetic atmosphere with my staff in the environment at MRD, and therefore my passions are fueled. Since 2003 I have been on the Board of Directors of Stepping Stone of SD. With my special events background I have been able to be very useful in fundraising and development. Many hours of joy go into this worthy cause and my friends in recovery.
